# Project Standards

## Migrations

- **Do not create new migrations** to add, delete, or modify columns on existing tables.
- **Only add migrations** for entirely new tables.
- To change an existing table: **edit the existing migration file**, then run `php artisan migrate:fresh` (or clear cache) and verify.

## Language and locale

- **Comments**: English only.
- **Code/DB**: Field and variable names in English.
- **User-facing strings** (HTML, labels, messages): **Translatable**; supported locales are **Catalan (ca)** and **Spanish / Castellano (es)**. No hardcoded UI strings; use Laravel lang keys or React i18n. See **`.cursor/rules/i18n.mdc`**.
- **Enums** (values shown to users): Store labels in lang files so they translate (e.g. `shop.status.pending` → "Pendent" / "Pendiente").

```php
// ✅ Comment in English; translation key for UI
$table->string('status')->comment('Order status'); // values from lang: shop.status.*
```

## Stack

- **Laravel as API + SPA (React).** Front-end talks to Laravel via **API REST**; React is the default UI. Laravel = backend, API routes, auth. Use **Blade only when necessary** (e.g. HTML shell that loads React, or a single login page if you keep it server-rendered). Do not use Inertia for this project.
- **Auth:** **Custom** (no Breeze). LoginController + session guard, like `~/Repos/abp-app`. See **`.cursor/rules/auth.mdc`**. See also **`.cursor/rules/react-use.mdc`**, **`.cursor/rules/api.mdc`**, **`.cursor/rules/security.mdc`**, **`.cursor/rules/i18n.mdc`**.

## Styling

- Use **Tailwind CSS** for all styling (utility-first, mobile-first). Use **daisyUI** for ready-made components (cards, modals, navbar, etc.); see **`.cursor/rules/daisyui.mdc`** and **`.cursor/rules/tailwind.mdc`**.
- Put theme tokens and overrides in a global **`styles.css`** (e.g. CSS variables, Tailwind/daisyUI theme). Add a separate CSS file per page or component only when the style does not repeat and is necessary.

## Product variants

- Products can optionally be grouped as **siblings** (variants) via **`product_variant_groups`**. A product belongs to at most one group (`products.variant_group_id`); products in the same group are "brothers" (e.g. same screw 30mm, 40mm, 50mm). No sort column: order variants by name or value in SQL (e.g. `ORDER BY name ASC`). See **`trash/diagramZero.dbml`** for the schema. Model: `ProductVariantGroup`, `Product::variantGroup()`, `Product::variantSiblings()`.

## Shared UI components

- **Page titles:** Use the shared **PageTitle** component (`resources/js/components/PageTitle.jsx`) for the main h1 on every content page (Cart, Orders, Products, Checkout, Profile, etc.). Do not use a raw `<h1 className="...">` for the page heading; keep the same style (bold, tracking-tight, border-bottom) everywhere. See **`.cursor/rules/components.mdc`**.
- Product grids and product tiles use the shared **ProductCard** component (`resources/js/components/ProductCard.jsx`). Use it on the home page (featured) and on the product list page so layout and behaviour stay consistent. See **`.cursor/rules/components.mdc`** for details and other shared components.

## Empty / missing data from the database

- When a field is expected from the API/DB and **nothing is received** (null, undefined, empty), render the field **blank** in the UI.
- **Do not** use placeholders such as em dash ("—"), "N/A", "–", or similar for missing values. Leave the cell or label content empty (e.g. `''` or nothing).

## Assets and build

- Use **Vite** for asset compilation (Laravel default). See **`.cursor/rules/vite.mdc`** for entry points. The main app is React; Blade is only for the HTML shell that loads the React bundle when needed.
